-- Japanese Bought Net 70.8 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 2012-06-20T23:52:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-20/japanese-bought-net-70-8-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended June 15 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 70.8 billion yen ($890.7 million)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 41.1 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 19.4 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 131.3 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 412.6 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 58.8 billion yen in stocks, and sold 1149.2 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net sale 677.8
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
